{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #684: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. For $0\\leq k\\leq n$ write\\[\\binom{n}{k} = uv\\]where the only primes dividing $u$ are in $[2,k]$ and the only primes dividing $v$ are in $(k,n]$.\n\nLet $f(n)$ be the smallest $k$ such that $u>n^2$. Give bounds for $f(n)$. Prize: no. OEIS: A392019. Tags: binomial coefficients, number theory, primes.","id":"vf_712b63cb8d91e817","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Partial result.","id":"vf_ae7c07921b7e634c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"OBLIGATION (Erdos #684). BANKED: f(M_K-1) > K verified for K=3..12 via Kummer no-carry (effective, subsequential lower bound). OPEN: promote the subsequential bound to the full claim for all n.","id":"vf_ba50ac1f1f60aa27","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdos #684: verified effective subsequential lower bound f(n) >= (1/2+o(1)) log n. Explicit construction M_K = prod_{p<=K} p^{floor(log_p K)+1}; computationally verified (K=3..12) that all v_p(C(M_K-1,k))=0 for p<=k<=K (no Kummer carries), so the smooth part u=1 < n^2 for every k<=K, hence f(M_K-1) > K; with log M_K = psi(K)+theta(K) = (2+o(1))K this gives the stated bound along n=M_K-1. The pointwise lower bound f(n)->infinity is known only INEFFECTIVELY (Mahler); this effective statement is subsequential, not pointwise. UPPER side (GPT-Pro, not re-verified here): an elementary Kummer+Dusart argument gives f(n) = O((log n)^2). UNVERIFIED claims (cited preprints not confirmable from here, treat with caution): an 'APSSV' optimized constant 24/(pi^2-6) and a 'Bae 2026' limsup f(n)/log n = infinity.","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_e61d7371f30c1be0","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"erdos-problems","